exports[`apiPageMarkdown library provenance block the druid page renders its component typedefs and pins to Insality/druid, not ts-defold/library 1`] = `
"# Insality / druid

\`druid\`

Entry point for Druid UI Framework.
Create a new Druid instance and adjust the Druid settings here.

- GitHub: [Insality/druid](https://github.com/Insality/druid) тАФ pinned to [\`1.2.5\`](https://github.com/Insality/druid/tree/1.2.5)
  1. Pick a release from [Insality/druid releases](https://github.com/Insality/druid/releases) and add its **Source code (zip)** URL (or a packaged \`.zip\` asset, if the library ships one) to \`game.project\` under \`[project]\` \`dependencies\`, then **Fetch Libraries** in the Defold editor.
  2. Run \`bunx @defold-typescript/cli resolve\` to materialize its types.
  3. Import it under a namespace alias of your choice:
     \`\`\`ts
     import * as druid from "druid"
     \`\`\`

## Functions

<div class="api-overview" aria-label="Function overview">

- [\`new(context: LuaTable, style: LuaTable | undefined): druid_instance\`](#newcontext-luatable-style-luatable--undefined-druid_instance)
- [\`register(name: string, module: LuaTable)\`](#registername-string-module-luatable)
- [\`set_default_style(style: LuaTable)\`](#set_default_stylestyle-luatable)
- [\`set_text_function(callback: (text_id: string) => string)\`](#set_text_functioncallback-text_id-string--string)
- [\`set_sound_function(callback: (sound_id: string) => void)\`](#set_sound_functioncallback-sound_id-string--void)
- [\`init_window_listener()\`](#init_window_listener)
- [\`on_window_callback(window_event: Opaque<"constant">)\`](#on_window_callbackwindow_event-opaqueconstant)
- [\`on_language_change()\`](#on_language_change)
- [\`get_widget<T extends druid_widget>(widget_class: T, gui_url: Url | string, params: unknown | undefined): T\`](#get_widgett-extends-druid_widgetwidget_class-t-gui_url-url--string-params-unknown--undefined-t)
- [\`register_druid_as_widget(druid: druid_instance)\`](#register_druid_as_widgetdruid-druid_instance)
- [\`unregister_druid_as_widget()\`](#unregister_druid_as_widget)
- [\`set_logger(logger_instance: druid_logger | LuaTable | undefined)\`](#set_loggerlogger_instance-druid_logger--luatable--undefined)
- [\`get_logger(name: string | undefined, level: string | undefined): druid_logger\`](#get_loggername-string--undefined-level-string--undefined-druid_logger)

</div>

### \`new(context: LuaTable, style: LuaTable | undefined): druid_instance\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Create a new Druid instance for creating GUI components.

**Parameters**

- \`context\`:тАВ\`LuaTable\` тАФ The Druid context. Usually, this is the self of the gui_script. It is passed into all Druid callbacks.
- \`style\`:тАВ\`LuaTable | undefined\` тАФ The Druid style table to override style parameters for this Druid instance.

**Returns**

- \`druid_instance\` тАФ The new Druid instance

</div>

### \`register(name: string, module: LuaTable)\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Register a new external Druid component.
Register component just makes the druid:new_{name} function.
For example, if you register a component called "my_component", you can create it using druid:new_my_component(...).
This can be useful if you have your own "basic" components that you don't want to require in every file.
The default way to create component is \`druid_instance:new(component_class, ...)\`.

**Parameters**

- \`name\`:тАВ\`string\` тАФ Module name
- \`module\`:тАВ\`LuaTable\` тАФ Lua table with component

</div>

### \`set_default_style(style: LuaTable)\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Set the default style for all Druid instances.

**Parameters**

- \`style\`:тАВ\`LuaTable\` тАФ Default style

</div>

### \`set_text_function(callback: (text_id: string) => string)\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Set the text function for the LangText component.

**Parameters**

- \`callback\`:тАВ\`(text_id: string) => string\` тАФ Get localized text function

</div>

### \`set_sound_function(callback: (sound_id: string) => void)\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Set the sound function to able components to play sounds.

**Parameters**

- \`callback\`:тАВ\`(sound_id: string) => void\` тАФ Sound play callback

</div>

### \`init_window_listener()\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Subscribe Druid to the window listener. It will override your previous
window listener, so if you have one, you should call M.on_window_callback manually.

</div>

### \`on_window_callback(window_event: Opaque<"constant">)\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Set the window callback to enable Druid window events.

**Parameters**

- \`window_event\`:тАВ\`Opaque<"constant">\` тАФ Event param from window listener

</div>

### \`on_language_change()\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Call this function when the game language changes.
It will notify all Druid instances to update the lang text components.

</div>

### \`get_widget<T extends druid_widget>(widget_class: T, gui_url: Url | string, params: unknown | undefined): T\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Create a widget from the bound Druid GUI instance.
The widget will be created and all widget functions can be called from Game Object contexts.
This allows using only \`druid_widget.gui_script\` for GUI files and call this widget functions from Game Object script file.
Widget class here is your lua file for the GUI scene (widgets in Druid)
<a href="/api/defold-1.13.0/msg#msgurlsocket-string--hash-path-string--hash-fragment-string--hash-url" class="symbol-xref">msg.url</a>(nil, nil, "gui_widget") -- current game object
<a href="/api/defold-1.13.0/msg#msgurlsocket-string--hash-path-string--hash-fragment-string--hash-url" class="symbol-xref">msg.url</a>(nil, object_url, "gui_widget") -- other game object

**Parameters**

- \`widget_class\`:тАВ\`T\` тАФ The class of the widget to return
- \`gui_url\`:тАВ\`Url | string\` тАФ GUI url or string of component name near current script
- \`params\`:тАВ\`unknown | undefined\` тАФ Additional parameters to pass to the widget's init function

**Returns**

- \`T\` тАФ The new created widget,

</div>

### \`register_druid_as_widget(druid: druid_instance)\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Bind a Druid GUI instance to the current game object.
This instance now can produce widgets from \`druid.get_widget()\` function.
Only one widget can be set per game object.

**Parameters**

- \`druid\`:тАВ\`druid_instance\` тАФ The druid instance to register

</div>

### \`unregister_druid_as_widget()\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Should be called on final, where druid instance is destroyed.

</div>

